# Unity Input System

Package `com.unity.inputsystem` is in the template manifest. **Do not use legacy `UnityEngine.Input`** for new code.

Scoped to input assets and **Gameplay** scripts — not `Assets/Game/UI/` (see `unity-ui.mdc`).

## Setup

1. **Project Settings → Player → Active Input Handling:** Input System Package (New) or Both
2. Template asset: `Assets/Game/Settings/Input/GameInputActions.inputactions` (Gameplay + UI maps)
3. Inspector → **Generate C# Class** if needed (template enables auto-generate to `Scripts/Runtime/Input/GameInputActions.cs`, namespace `Game.Input`)

## Generated class pattern (preferred)

Place gameplay input readers in `Scripts/Runtime/Gameplay/`, namespace `Game.Gameplay`:

```
using UnityEngine;
using UnityEngine.InputSystem;
using Game.Input;

namespace Game.Gameplay
{
    public class PlayerInputController : MonoBehaviour
    {
        private PlayerInputActions _inputActions;

        public Vector2 MoveInput { get; private set; }

        private void Awake() => _inputActions = new PlayerInputActions();

        private void OnEnable()
        {
            _inputActions.Gameplay.Jump.performed += OnJump;
            _inputActions.Gameplay.Enable();
        }

        private void OnDisable()
        {
            _inputActions.Gameplay.Jump.performed -= OnJump;
            _inputActions.Gameplay.Disable();
        }

        private void Update()
        {
            MoveInput = _inputActions.Gameplay.Move.ReadValue<Vector2>();
        }

        private void OnJump(InputAction.CallbackContext ctx)
        {
            if (ctx.performed) { /* jump */ }
        }
    }
}
```

## Rules

- Subscribe in `OnEnable`, unsubscribe in `OnDisable` — use named handlers, not lambdas (avoid duplicate subs)
- Continuous values (`Move`, `Look`): read in `Update`; buttons: `performed` / `ReadValueAsButton`
- **PlayerInput** component: OK for quick setup or local multiplayer (`PlayerInputManager`); generated class preferred for gameplay code
- Manual `InputActionAsset`: enable/disable the **action map**, not individual actions ad hoc
- Rebinding: `PerformInteractiveRebinding()`; persist overrides via `SaveBindingOverridesAsJson()` when needed

See `unity-docs.mdc` → @Docs **Input System 1.19**.
